methods.accept:
Provides a value to this consumer.  A false return value indicates that the application
 providing values to this consumer should not invoke it again.

:param v: (long) - the value
:return: (boolean) false if don't want any more values after this one, true otherwise.

text:
Note this is similar to java.util.function.LongPredicate; we don't use that
 since it could create confusion as for intended semantics for use.
